At least 30 people are dead and dozens missing after the MV Shariatpur 1 ferry carrying 200 people collides with an oil tanker. It capsizes on the Meghna River in Bangladesh's Munshiganj District near the capital Dhaka. (AP via Brisbane Times) (BBC) (The Telegraph) (AP via Newsday)Two trains crash in the small Polish town of Szczekociny near Zawiercie, with 13 people killed and up to 50 people injured. (BBC) (AP via Google) (Reuters via MSNBC)